{"info": {"author": "Jonas Eriksson", "author_email": "jonas@upto.se", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "How to use\n==========\nSee `examples/`\n\nDependencies\n============\n\nDebian/Ubuntu\n-------------\n```\n# Common\n$ sudo apt install python3-parted python3-distutils\n# FAT support\n$ sudo apt install dosfstools mtools\n# ext* support\n$ sudo apt install e2fsprogs\n# All\n$ sudo apt install python3-parted python3-distutils dosfstools mtools e2fsprogs\n```\n\nFedora/CentOS\n-------------\n```\n# Common\n$ sudo dnf install python3-pyparted\n# FAT support\n$ sudo dnf install dosfstools mtools\n# ext* support\n$ sudo dnf install e2fsprogs\n# All\n$ sudo dnf install python3-pyparted dosfstools mtools e2fsprogs\n```\n\n\nKnown issues\n============\n`mtools` and `debugfs` is not good at error reporting, so if a copy fails it\nmight not show until you try to mount the image.\n\nParted misbehaves on some platforms (Debian 10), and shrinks partitions. Use\nSfdisk instead. Additionally, some FAT implementations expect the file system\nto have exactly the same size as the partition, and thus padding them will not\nwork, unless done exactly.\n\n`copy_file_range` seems to misbehave in containers sometimes, observed on\nFedora 30 + podman with Debian 10 container where it skips to copy some data.\n\nFuture\n======\n- Configurable alignment, defaulting to 1MiB\n- Optional cleaning (\"always\", \"not on error\", \"never\")\n- Proper naive `copy_file_range` function, using `dup()`\n- Integrated and automated tests\n- GPT for sfdisk partitioner\n- Multiboot images (iso, efi, bios)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/zqad/simplediskimage/", "keywords": "", "license": "Apache-2.0", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "simplediskimage", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/simplediskimage/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/simplediskimage/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/zqad/simplediskimage/"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/simplediskimage/0.2/", "requires_dist": ["pyparted"], "requires_python": ">=3.4", "summary": "Library used to build simple disk images with multiple partitions", "version": "0.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>How to use</h1>\n<p>See <code>examples/</code></p>\n<h1>Dependencies</h1>\n<h2>Debian/Ubuntu</h2>\n<pre><code># Common\n$ sudo apt install python3-parted python3-distutils\n# FAT support\n$ sudo apt install dosfstools mtools\n# ext* support\n$ sudo apt install e2fsprogs\n# All\n$ sudo apt install python3-parted python3-distutils dosfstools mtools e2fsprogs\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Fedora/CentOS</h2>\n<pre><code># Common\n$ sudo dnf install python3-pyparted\n# FAT support\n$ sudo dnf install dosfstools mtools\n# ext* support\n$ sudo dnf install e2fsprogs\n# All\n$ sudo dnf install python3-pyparted dosfstools mtools e2fsprogs\n</code></pre>\n<h1>Known issues</h1>\n<p><code>mtools</code> and <code>debugfs</code> is not good at error reporting, so if a copy fails it\nmight not show until you try to mount the image.</p>\n<p>Parted misbehaves on some platforms (Debian 10), and shrinks partitions. Use\nSfdisk instead. Additionally, some FAT implementations expect the file system\nto have exactly the same size as the partition, and thus padding them will not\nwork, unless done exactly.</p>\n<p><code>copy_file_range</code> seems to misbehave in containers sometimes, observed on\nFedora 30 + podman with Debian 10 container where it skips to copy some data.</p>\n<h1>Future</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Configurable alignment, defaulting to 1MiB</li>\n<li>Optional cleaning (\"always\", \"not on error\", \"never\")</li>\n<li>Proper naive <code>copy_file_range</code> function, using <code>dup()</code></li>\n<li>Integrated and automated tests</li>\n<li>GPT for sfdisk partitioner</li>\n<li>Multiboot images (iso, efi, bios)</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6963987, "releases": {"0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "da74802876b2550e210482c7f1a16a78", "sha256": "f3eb18e03727707c4510479ae07cfa6e8a7598bf77ca0130de003de528e06b40"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "simplediskimage-0.1.1-py3.7.egg", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "da74802876b2550e210482c7f1a16a78", "packagetype": "bdist_egg", "python_version": "3.7", "requires_python": ">=3.4", "size": 30527, "upload_time": "2020-04-06T11:49:10", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-06T11:49:10.294566Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/85/dd/3ea98f23ae7e7e7e335df7c16b312c0fbd1732b18a83e444bb234ec0c1e2/simplediskimage-0.1.1-py3.7.egg", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e8131685c4894c383a4f9cfdd3c46849", "sha256": "f559642710c65db1d1d28acaff3e98f5695f508bd40bd339877a7299cdd527ff"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "simplediskimage-0.1.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e8131685c4894c383a4f9cfdd3c46849", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.4", "size": 15666, "upload_time": "2020-04-06T12:32:47", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-06T12:32:47.393580Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/bb/d9/f4f166bab9f373267b1eafcc4775984c3c334afc0aab36b2f472d67b3a74/simplediskimage-0.1.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "dda5197b21faa76d5021eb03b03c2637", "sha256": "d5e3586d6bfda2c604f4c05b0f0ba792c71ddb4ab21d255d7be47873f7826b52"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "simplediskimage-0.1.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "dda5197b21faa76d5021eb03b03c2637", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.4", "size": 12325, "upload_time": "2020-04-06T